Package suggestions

Class Suggestion

  • Object
    • Suggestion
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    public class Suggestion
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Represents a Suggestion entry created in the SuggestionsDB database. A suggestion entry contains information related to a suggestion that a camp committee member sends about a camp.
    Since:
    2023-11-17
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Soo Qi Yang, Teo Kai Xuan, Masagca Merwyn Louie Dumasis, Nguyen Phuong Linh, Tee Jeeng Yee
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • Suggestion

        public Suggestion​(int suggestionID,
                  String camp,
                  String text,
                  String user)
        Creates a new Suggestion with the given attributes. The suggestion is not approved initially. The last edit date is initially set to the date the suggestion was created. The date the suggestion has to be approved by is set to be 5 days from the date that the suggestion was made, by default.
        Parameters:
        suggestionID - The unique suggestion number of this suggestion. Assignment is handled by SuggestionsDB database.
        camp - The name of the camp that this suggestion is about.
        text - The suggestion text.
        user - The name of the camp committee member that suggested this suggestion.
